{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in Modify EPS Bearer Context Reject message decoding\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE NAS layer contained a memory leak when decoding Modify EPS Bearer Context Reject messages with Protocol Configuration Options. The leak occurred when the decode function was called multiple times on the same message structure or when decoding failed partway through processing optional fields.\n\nThe issue was introduced during the initial implementation of the Protocol Configuration Options decoding logic, where allocated memory was not properly freed in error paths or when overwriting existing data.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/ESM/MSG/ModifyEpsBearerContextReject.c`: Added check to free existing protocol configuration options before decoding new ones and provided cleanup function.\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/ESM/MSG/ModifyEpsBearerContextReject.h`: Added declaration for cleanup function.\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/ProtocolConfigurationOptions.c`: Enhanced error handling to free partially allocated memory and added proper cleanup function.\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/ProtocolConfigurationOptions.h`: Added declaration for cleanup function.\n\n"
}